anch of Philosophy that undermined you asking the question in the first place.\", \"from\": 382, \"to\": 636, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 435, \"end\": 452, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Modern_philosophy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Modern Philosophy\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Modern_philosophy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Modern_philosophy\"}, {\"begin\": 511, \"end\": 516, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazism\", \"score\": 0.9992273066885564, \"rank\": 0.0007715594025552505, \"text\": \"Nazis\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazism\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Are not you French\\\"?\", \"from\": 638, \"to\": 659, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Oui\\\"  \\\"Did not you all roll over for the Nazis so your pretty art would not get smashed\\\"  \\\"Are not we all French, and dying anyway\\\".\", \"from\": 661, \"to\": 794, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 703, \"end\": 708, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazism\", \"score\": 0.9992273066885564, \"rank\": 0.0007715594025552505, \"text\": \"Nazis\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazism\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"You are dark and complicated, how can I please you\\\".\", \"from\": 796, \"to\": 849, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"How French.\", \"from\": 851, \"to\": 862, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If Earth ever gets invaded by Aliens seeking to destroy us, only the French would try and cut a deal with them.\", \"from\": 864, \"to\": 975, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 894, \"end\": 900, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Extraterrestrial_life\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9221060793552884e-29, \"text\": \"Aliens\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Extraterrestrial_life\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Extraterrestrial_life\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So fuck the French, but we can still enjoy their culture and art until the planet burns, and when that happens we should use Paris as the kindling.\", \"from\": 977, \"to\": 1124, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1102, \"end\": 1107, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999996500719, \"rank\": 3.500063062137281e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I am no fan of sport.\", \"from\": 1126, \"to\": 1147, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Do not get me wrong.\", \"from\": 1149, \"to\": 1169, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I appreciate the skill set required to do what they do, but my hero's are artists, philosophers, engineers, thinkers - not Sportspeople, but even I take time to watch the Olympics and it was an amazing journey.\", \"from\": 1171, \"to\": 1381, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris Olympics was a cacophony of culture, meritocracy and the beauty of competition (pity about the Genocide in Gaza, sewage and the burning planet).\", \"from\": 1383, \"to\": 1537, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1488, \"end\": 1496, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Genocide\", \"score\": 0.9999999997100986, \"rank\": 2.8942299130153297e-10, \"text\": \"Genocide\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Genocide\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Genocide\"}, {\"begin\": 1500, \"end\": 1504, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_City\", \"score\": 0.9811703574214782, \"rank\": 0.0191910022917771, \"text\": \"Gaza\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_City\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There was magic, there was drama and there was naked dripping transphobia.\", \"from\": 1539, \"to\": 1613, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympics are a hope tha